snippet.title: Rotten Tomatoes
snippet.description:
Since 1998, Rotten Tomatoes has been delivering critical hits with the world-famous Tomatometer™. What’s a Tomatometer, you ask? It's the most trusted resource for professional reviews of movies and TV shows. The Tomatometer measures the percentage of positive reviews from hundreds of professional critics and publications, and it will tell you if the critics agree if a movie is Fresh or Rotten. We also deliver up the latest news from Hollywood, and plenty of interviews with filmmakers and stars. We may be called "Rotten Tomatoes," but we'll always have something fresh for you to see!

We’re building a community for movie and TV lovers to share their opinions and we want you to join us.  We’re all about healthy discussion and debate, but we do have some house rules we need you to respect so that the comment section is useful and enjoyable for everyone.

Please read our Comment Policy before commenting. http://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/otg-article/community-code-of-conduct/
